At least two persons were burnt to death in the violence that hit Kano during the parliamentary and presidential elections. The New Nigerian Peoples Party, NNPP, campaign office in Tudun Wada Local Government Area of Kano State has also been burnt down. Kano State Police Command Public Relations Officer, SP Abdullahi Haruna Kiyawa, who confirmed the incidents said an official of the Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC, was attacked in Takai Local Government Area of the state. He said when the thugs set the party’s office on fire, “two unknown persons in a stationary vehicle inside the building of the political campaign office of the House of Representatives candidate of NNPP were burnt to death.”